  "description": "On my Omnibook, I\u0026rsquo;m running Windows 11, with Windows Subsystem for Linux hosting Ubuntu. I\u0026rsquo;d like to, within this stack, set up Guix, because after mucking about for a few months, I\u0026rsquo;m back to remembering that my old MUD designing brought me to it, after moving me from Python to Racket to Fennel. According to the Guix Manual, I can simply =sudo apt install guix= and =sudo guix pull= , so I\u0026rsquo;ve started that, which as started a\u0026hellip; very slow download of the Guix source code, I think.\n",
